    description:
      "Treasure Case 2024 T698One Roman solidus. Part of&nbsp;LIN-483FDE coin hoard.Coin 1A gold Roman solidus of Honorius (AD&nbsp;395-423), dating to the period c.AD 395-402 (Reece period 21).&nbsp;Obverse D N HONORI-VS P F AVG, pearl-diademed, draped and cuirassed bust, right. VICTORI-A AVGGG reverse depicting the emperor standing right, holding a standard and Victory-on-globe with his foot on a fallen captive. Mint of&nbsp;Milan: M&nbsp;D//COMOB. Hoxne no. 42;&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;X, p. 318, no.1206.Diameter: 20.93 mm; Thickness: 1.21 mm; Weight: 4.54g.&nbsp; Die Axis: 6.DiscussionThis solidus was found near to a similar coin of Honorious&nbsp;with VICTOR-IA AVGGG reverse, found while metal-detecting and reported to the Historic Environment Record in 1989 (Bland and Loriot 2010, no. 373). The discovery of a second coin of the same type and location indicates a dispersed coin hoard. A third&nbsp;solidus (mint of&nbsp;Ravenna) was found by the same finder on 24th October 2024 in the same area and is&nbsp;consequently an addendum to this treasure case.This is the second example of a solidus coin hoard in Lincolnshire recorded by the Portable Antiquities Scheme,&nbsp;the other example includes three coins of Gratian, Valentinian and Theodosius (LIN-718484;&nbsp;2005T292).&nbsp;Roman solidus of Honorius are uncommon discoveries&nbsp;as a single find, with only 13 examples recorded on the Portable Antiquities Scheme (PAS) database. This is the first example included in a coin hoard recorded by the PAS and is therefore a &#39;find of note&#39;.References citedBland, R. and Loriot, X., 2010. Roman and Early Byzantine gold coins found in Britain and Ireland.&nbsp;Royal Numismatic Society Special Publication,&nbsp;46.",
