      "A disturbed coin hoard of 12 late roman silver siliquae&nbsp;found within a spread of 0.5m square dating between&nbsp;AD 353 &ndash; 367and&nbsp;probably deposited/lost in the late 4th or early 5th century.&nbsp;Coin 1: a Roman silver&nbsp;siliqua of&nbsp;Constantius II (AD 337-361), dating to the period c. AD 359-361.&nbsp;(Reece period 18). VOTIS XXX MVLTIS XXXX reverse. Mint of Arles C.f. RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp 224 ff., no: 261/291. Diameter: 17.36mm; weight: 1.67g. DA: 11. Obverse:&nbsp; pearl diademed, draped and cuirassed bust right;legend:&nbsp;D N CONSTAN-TIVS P F AVG.&nbsp;Reverse:&nbsp;Wreath with&nbsp;VOTIS XXX MVLTIS XXXX. Mint mark: -//PCON.&nbsp;Coin 2: a Roman silver&nbsp;siliqua of&nbsp;Constantius II (AD337-361), dating to the period c. AD 359-361.&nbsp;(Reece period 18). &nbsp;VOTIS XXX MVLTIS XXXX reverse. Mint of Arles C.f. RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp 224 ff., no: 261/291. Diameter: 18.28mm; weight: 2.18g. DA: 11. Obverse:&nbsp; pearl diademed, draped and cuirassed bust right; legend:&nbsp;D N CONSTAN-TIVS P F AVG.&nbsp;Reverse:&nbsp;Wreath with&nbsp;VOTIS XXX MVLTIS XXXX. Mint mark: -//PCON. There is a crack in the flan at the top of the obverse.&nbsp;Coin 3: &nbsp;a Roman silver&nbsp;siliqua with the obverse of Constantius II (AD 337-361) and reverse of Julian, VOTIS V MVLT&nbsp;X, dating to the period c. AD&nbsp;360-363. (Reece period 18). Mint of Lyons. For reverse, see&nbsp;RIC VIII p.195, no: 229. Poor style, probably a contemporary copy. Diameter: 17.90mm; weight: 2.00g. DA: 1. Obverse: pearl diademed, draped and cuirassed bust right: legend: DN CONSTAN-TIVS PF AVG. Reverse: wreath with VOT V MVLT X. Mint mark: LVG.Coin 4: a&nbsp;reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;of Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD 360-3), dating to the period AD 360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOTIS V&nbsp;MVLTIS X&nbsp;reverse. Trier&nbsp;mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp.168 no: 364. &nbsp;Diameter: 17.67mm; weight: 1.41g. DA:12.&nbsp;Obverse:&nbsp;pearl diademed draped and cuirassed&nbsp;bust right; legend: DN&nbsp;CL IVLI-ANVS&nbsp;AVG.&nbsp;Reverse: wreath with VOTIS/[V]/MVLTIS/X. Mint Mark: -//TR.&nbsp;&nbsp;Possibly irregular.Coin 5: a&nbsp;reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD&nbsp;360-3), dating to the period&nbsp;AD&nbsp;360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOT X MVLT XX reverse. Arles&nbsp;mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp.228 no: 309.&nbsp;&nbsp;Diameter: 18.07mm; weight: 2.00g. DA:7.&nbsp;Obverse:&nbsp;pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bearded&nbsp;bust right; legend: DN FL CL IVL[I]-ANVS P F&nbsp;AVG.&nbsp;Reverse: legend in wreath with medallion containing eagle.&nbsp;VOT/X/MVLT/XX. Mint Mark: -//[S]CONST.Coin 6: a&nbsp;reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD&nbsp;360-3), dating to the period&nbsp;AD&nbsp;360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOT X MVLT XX reverse. Arles&nbsp;mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp.228 no: 309.&nbsp;Diameter: 17.73mm; weight: 2.00g. DA:12.&nbsp;Obverse:&nbsp;pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bearded&nbsp;bust right; legend: DN FL CL IVLI-ANVS PF&nbsp;AVG.&nbsp;Reverse: legend in wreath with medallion containing eagle with head l.&nbsp;&nbsp;VOT/X/MVLT/XX. Mint Mark: -//TCONST.&nbsp;Coin 7: A&nbsp;reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;of Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD 360-3),&nbsp;dating to the period AD 360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOT X MVLT XX reverse. Lyon mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp.195 no: 234. Diameter: 17.81mm; weight: 1.29g. DA:11. A short section of the flan is missing with some of the mintmark.&nbsp;Obverse:&nbsp;pearl diademed draped and cuirassed unbearded&nbsp;bust right; legend:DN FL CL IVLI-ANVS PF&nbsp;AVG.&nbsp;Reverse: wreath with VOT/X/MVLT/XX. Mint Mark: -//[PL]VG. Possibly irregular.Coin 8: A lightly clipped reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;of Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD 360-3),&nbsp;dating to the period AD 360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOT X MVLT XX reverse. Lyon mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII Lyon, pp.195 no&#39;s: 231-232. Diameter: 16.82mm; weight: 1.50g. DA:6.&nbsp;Obverse: pearl diademed draped and cuirassed&nbsp;&#39;bearded&#39;&nbsp;bust right; legend: FL CL IVLIA-NVS PP AV[G].&nbsp;This example is bearded where as listed in RIC and Hoxne as unbearded.&nbsp;Reverse: wreath with VOT/X/MVLT/XX. Mint Mark: -//LVG.Coin 9: A&nbsp;reduced silver Roman siliqua of&nbsp;of Julian II&nbsp;as Augustus (AD 360-3), dating to the period AD 360-363. (Reece Period 18). VOT X MVLT XX reverse. Arles&nbsp;mint. Cf.&nbsp;RIC&nbsp;VIII, pp.228 no: 311. &nbsp;Diameter: 18.10mm; weight: 2.22g. DA:6.&nbsp;Obverse:&nbsp;pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bearded&nbsp;bust right; legend:DN FL CL IVLIA-NVS PF&nbsp;AVG.&nbsp;Reverse: wreath with VOT/X/MVLT/XX. Mint Mark: -//P CONST. The flan has a large nick and crack at the base of the obverse.&nbsp;Coin 10: a silver roman siliqua of Valentinian I (AD 364-375), dating to the period AD 364-367. (Reece period 19). RESTITV-TOR REIP reverse. Lyon mint. cf. RIC IX, pp. 43, no: 6b. Measurements: diameter: 17.68mm; weight; 2.42g. DA: 12.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obverse: pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bust right; legend: DN VALENTINI-ANVS PF AVG. Reverse: emperor standing facing head right. holding labarum with hook on shaft and victory on globe. Legend: RESTITV-TOR [REIP]. Mint Mark: -//PLVG[&bull;]Coin 11: &nbsp;a silver roman siliqua of Valentinian I (AD 364-375), dating to the period AD 364-367. (Reece period 19). RESTITV-TOR REIP reverse. Lyon mint. cf. RIC IX, pp. 43, no: 6a. Measurements: diameter: 18.68mm; weight; 1.93g. DA: 6..&nbsp;&nbsp;Obverse: pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bust right; legend: DN VALENTINI-ANVS PF AVG. Reverse: emperor standing facing head right. holding labarum with hook on shaft and victory on globe. Legend: RESTITV-TOR REIP. Mint Mark: -//SLVG.Coin 12: Contemporary copy of a silver Roman&nbsp;siliqua of Valentinian I (AD&nbsp;364-375), dating to the period&nbsp;AD&nbsp;364-367. (Reece period 19). Lyon mint. Measurements: diameter: 16.75mm; weight; 1.61g. DA: 11.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obverse: pearl diademed draped and cuirassed bust right; legend: DN VALENT[I]-[NI]ANVS&nbsp;[PF AVG]. &nbsp;Reverse: emperor standing facing head right. holding labarum&nbsp;and victory on globe. Legend: RESTITVTOR-REIPVBLICAE. Mint Mark: -//LVG.Discussion: A radiate of Postumus&nbsp;was also found within the area of the scattered hoard&nbsp;&nbsp;(SUSS-20891D);&nbsp;but it has been excluded from the case as it is unlikely to be part of the hoard due to its earlier date and lower silver content. The coins date between AD 353 and 367. They are generally lightly worn suggesting they were not in circulation for too long before loss or deposition which is suggested as being in the late 4th to early 5th century.",
