    notes:
      "The coins were found in close proximity and are more than 10% precious metal and&nbsp;are over 300 years old. The group&nbsp;consequently qualify&nbsp;as Treasure under the stipulations of the Treasure Act 1996 in terms of both age and precious metal content.Associated artefacts (with image no.) - Eleanore Cox26 An incomplete copper alloy ring of uncertain date (AD&nbsp;43-1900). The object is semi-circular in plan and circular in section with tapering terminals which terminate in old abraded breaks. The surface is heavily abraded and corroded. The metal is light brown in colour. Length: 18.46mm, Width: 7.33mm, Thickness: 2.79mm, Weight: 0.6g74. A complete copper alloy toggle of Iron Age to Early-Roman date (200&nbsp;BC&nbsp;-&nbsp;AD&nbsp;100). The object is a bar-shaped toggle. The toggle has a swollen central section, oval in plan and section with flat top and bottom sides and a central circular hole passing through the centre from top to bottom. To either side of the central section are circular sectioned projections ending in flattened knops. The projections are waisted (narrowed) with each end having a narrowed circular terminal. There are incised circumferential grooves flanking the ventral hole and on the inner side of the projections.&nbsp;The metal is brown with areas of light brown corrosion.Length: 37.65mm, Width: 13.88mm, Thickness: 9.48mm, &nbsp;Diameter (lobe): 12.13mm, Diameter (perforation): 7.90mm, Weight: 16.9g75. An incomplete copper-alloy Colchester derivative, Harlow, double lug brooch of Roman date (AD&nbsp;43-100). The object is a sprung form. The object is composed of hollow circular wings, to the back of which is an integral double perforated attachment loop with two sections of circular sectioned wire retained. The head of the brooch has a rectangular central projection which descends a short way down the head. From the wings the bow projects in a D shape. The bow terminates below the head in a transverse abraded break.The metal is mid-green in colour with a predominantly smooth patina.Mackreth 2011, CD Ha 3.a2. Plate 34Length: 13.41mm, Width: 21.63mm, Thickness: 8.83mm, Weight: 2.5g",
