    subperiodFrom: "Early",
    description:
      "Two Roman Republican silver denarii dating to the 1st century BC.Description:Coin 1 - Found by Mr. Raymond Piper: A heavily worn silver Roman Republican denarius, possibly issued by C. Vibius Pansa, c. 90 BC. Obverse Laureate head of Apollo right. Legend possibly '[PANSA]', now illegible. Reverse type Minerva in fast quadriga right, crowned by Victory, holding spear and reins in left hand and trophy in right. Legend possibly '[C VIBIVS C F]' in exergue. Probably RRC 342/5 (Crawford 1975). The coin is too worn to be conclusively identified.Measurements: Uncertain, none listed in previous report or record and no scale in image.Coin 2 - Found by Mr Steven Long: A worn silver Roman Republican denarius issued by P. Clodius M. f. at Rome during 42 BC. Obverse: 'Laureate head of Apollo right, lyre behind.', No legend. Reverse type Diana Lucifera standing right, lit long torch in each hand, bow and quiver across shoulder. Legend reads top to bottom 'P CLODIVS' right, 'M.F.' left. RRC 494/23 (Crawford 1975).Measurements: 18mm in diameter and weight of 3.4gDiscussion: This find of two Roman republican silver coins with no early Roman activity in the area suggests that these coins relate to the same loss or depositional event. Whether this is a dispersed hoard, votive deposit or purse loss it is not possible to be sure. It should be noted however that the coins were found in an area of high late Iron Age activity which included a large dispersed potin hoard or hoards which the coins were brought in with, see KENT-B3CDF1 (2011T585) KENT-A07E23 (2017T132) and KENT-588B4F (2017T606). The Republican coins are however significantly later than the Potin hoard, show significant wear and are of types known to be circulating into the 1st century AD.Conclusion:It is therefore likely that these coins belong to the same find and thus, as they are both silver coins, older than 300 years old and found in close association they constitute potential Treasure under the stipulations of The Treasure Act 1996.",
