      "It is therefore clear that this hoard contains more than 2 silver or gold coins over 300 years old and thus constitutes potential Treasure under the stipulations of The Treasure Act 1996.Johns, C.M. 1979. The Whorlton (Yorkshire) Hoard (1810). In R.A.G. Carson and A. M. Burnett eds. Coin Hoards from Roman Britain I. British Museum Occasional Paper 5, 110?117.Moorhead S. and Walton, P. 2014. Coinage at the End of Roman Britain. In: F. K. Haarer, R. Collins, K. Fitzpatrick-Matthews, S. Moorhead, D. Petts & P. Walton (eds.), 2014. AD 410: The History and Archaeology of Late and Post-Roman Britain. Oxford: Society for the Promotion of Roman Studies, 100-116.",
