      "Treasure Case 2016 T959; disclaimed, returned to finder (But three coins donated to BM).Chaffcombe, Somerset211 sestertii and lower denominations to AD 198 (+ 7 stray radiates / nummus)Summary (addenda coins marked *)sestertii and lower denominations:Claudian copy (mid 1stC), 1?Domitian (AD 81-96), 1 + 1*Trajan (AD 98-117), 3 + 3*Hadrian (AD 117-138), 9 + 6*Antoninus Pius (AD 138-161), 5 + 7*Faustina I, 4*Marcus Caesar, 2 + 2*Faustina II, 1*Marcus Aurelius (AD 161-180), 8 + 13*Lucius Verus, 1*Marcus or Verus, 2*Faustina II, 3 + 2*Diva Faustina II, 1Lucilla, 2Commodus under Marcus, 1 + 2*Commodus (AD 180-192), 1 + 3*Divus Marcus Aurelius, 1Uncertain Antonine Emperor, 4Uncertain Antonine Empress, 6 + 3*Septimius Severus - Wars of Succession (AD 193-198)Julia Domna, 1 + 1*Irregular (limesfalsa), 1*Emperor illegible, 60 + 50* (incl. minor frags)Total = 109 + 102*Stray coins:radiatesDivus Clausdius (AD 270), 1*Victorinus (AD 269-71), 1Tetricus I (AD 271-4), 1Probus (AD 276-82), 1*Carausius (AD 286-93), 1*Allectus (AD 293-6), 1Nummus2nd reign of Maximian (AD 307-10), 1*",
