    description:
      "Second addendum to the Marham hoard which is otherwise recorded at .NMS-3EF493 (2013 T420 and 2014 T83) and summary at IARCH-677D3D.Description: 5 copper alloy Roman radiates, 3 of Carausius (AD 286-93) and 2 of Allectus (AD 293-6), forming part of a dispersed hoard. Two groups of coins were recovered previously, 14 in 2013 (2013 T420) and a further 8 in 2014 (2014 T836). This latest addition brings the total number of coins up to 27. As noted in the report for the original group, most of the coins are corroded, but appear to have been in good condition when deposited. It was proposed that the hoard was likely deposited c. AD 296, possibly as a result of the re-conquest of Britain by Constantius Chlorus. Given the de-monetisation of these coins shortly afterwards, the hoard cannot have been deposited much later. This latest group of coins sits well within the existing group and does not alter the original interpretation.",
