    description:
      "A group of 19 silver coins, eight Roman denarii and eleven Icenian silver units found during Archaeological excavation over a small area. They clearly represent a hoard dispersed at some point in the past. Judging by the relatively high levels of wear on the latest closely datable coin, a denarius of Augustus struck c.19BC (coin 7), this hoard was probably lost or deposited in the mid-first century AD. It is tempting to connect it with either the Roman invasion of AD43 or the Boudiccan revolt of AD60/61. It thus parallels a number of mixed hoards of Roman denarii and Icenian silver units from elsewhere in Norfolk.CatalogueRoman coins1. Republican denarius, Rome, Crawford 299/1a, weight (incomplete) 1.88g, 111-110BC (SF 41)2. Republican denarius, Q. Titius, Rome, Crawford 341/1, weight (incomplete) 3.08g, 90BC (SF 74)3. Republican denarius, L. Rutilius Flaccus, Rome, Crawford 387/1, 77BC, weight 3.38g (SF 72)4. Marcus Antonius, Eastern mint travelling with Antonius, Crawford 544/17 (LEG IV), weight 2.52g, 32-31BC (SF 69)5. Marcus Antonius, Eastern mint travelling with Antonius, Crawford 544/17 (LEG IV), weight 3.07g, 32-31BC (SF 73)6. Marcus Antonius, Eastern mint travelling with Antonius, Crawford 544/?29 (probably LEG XIV), weight 2.86g, 32-31BC (SF 40)7. Augustus, denarius, Spanish mint, RIC I, 86a, weight 3.17g, 19BC (SF 38)8. Two small denarius fragments, probably Republican and probably from the same coin, further details illegible, weights 0.47g and 0.36g, probably 1st century BC (SF 44)Iron Age coins9. Icenian silver unit, Boar-Horse type, weight 0.72g (SF 71)10. Icenian silver unit, Boar-Horse type, weight (incomplete) 0.58g (SF 68)11. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse ANTED type, weight 0.85g (SF 66)12. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse ECEN type, weight 0.87g (SF 70)13. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse ECEN type, weight 0.71g (SF 65)14. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse ECEN type with horse left, weight 0.62g (SF 8)15. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse ECEN type, weight (incomplete) 0.49g (SF 103)16. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse type, weight 0.80g (SF 39)17. Icenian silver unit, Pattern-Horse type, weight 0.67g (SF 43)18. Icenian silver unit, Late Face-Horse type, weight 0.89g (SF 67)19. Icenian silver unit, Late Face-Horse type, weight (incomplete) 0.67g (SF 42)",
