    notes:
      "The coins are copper-alloy Roman pieces known as Nummi. Almost all of the coins belong to the Late Roman period dating to a range of period between AD 322 and 340. Due to the state of most of the coins, it is not possible to determine the emperor named in the legends so the coins are attributed to a general period of the House of Constantine. The earliest coin legible and the only one is possible to ascribe to an Emperor is a Nummus of Constantine I dating to AD 322-325.",
