    notes:
      "DiscussionThe termination date of this hoard makes it one of the latest to have been recovered from the north-west counties, a point emphasised by the fact that eight of the twenty-three coins were issued from the mid-370s onwards.Only one other hoard of siliquae of the late fourth century has been recorded from the North West - that consisting of 401 coins, ranging in date from Constantius II to Honorius, which is said to have been found at Rossall Point (near Fleetwood in Lancashire) in the 1840s. This hoard is now in the collection of the Harris Museum in Preston. However, there are difficulties regarding the true provenance of this hoard:D. Shotter",
