    description:
      "Found with the aid of a metal detector, 2013. This debased radiate hoard was clearly quite scattered as it was found with late Roman bronzes of other periods. The material from Valerian to the Tetrici seems to form a discrete group, with the coins of Carausius also regarded as part of this hoard.The proportion of Victorinus to Tetricus in Normanby, a radiate hoard closing with the earlier coins of Carausius is 1:2.8. For Marlborough it is 1:2. Thus the current hoard seems to have an earlier composition than Normanby as well as the obviously large gap between AD 274 and AD 286. Nevertheless the Carausian coins present are all from the earliest part of the reign so they must remain plausible as hoard material and they are included in this catalogue for this reason as well as their numismatic interest.Note: an additional 16 stray fourth century nummi were reported with the hoard.Summary:Central empire\t\t\tQty.\t\tValerian, AD 253-60\t\t\t\t\t\t1\t\t\t\t\tSalonina (joint reign)\t\t\t1\t\tGallienus, sole reign (AD 260-8)\t\t\t43\t\tSalonina (sole reign)\t\t\t4\t\tClaudius II\t\t\t47\t\tDivus Claudius\t\t\t9\t\tQuintillus\t\t\t3\t\t\t\t\tGallic empire\t\t\t\t\t\tQty.\t\tPostumus\t\t\t6\t\tVictorinus\t\t\t75\t\tTetricus I\t\t\t101\t\tTetricus II\t\t\t49\t\tUncertain Gallic emperor\t\t\t40\t\tIllegible radiates\t\t\t53\t\tIrregular radiates\t\t\t29\t\tBritish empire\t\t\tQty.\t\tCarausius (AD 286-93)\t\t\t\t\t\t6 (all unmintmarked; c. AD 286-9)\t\t\t\t\tTotal (hoard) \t\t\t465\t\tStray coins:Nummi:Tetrarchic (AD 293-310) 1Constantinian (AD 330-5) 2Constantinian (AD 346-8) 1Valentinianic (AD 364-78) 9Theodosian (AD 378/9-95) 1 (of Gratian, d.AD 383)Illegible 2Total (stray coins) 16",
