      "CORONER'S REPORT13 Bronze Coins (sestertius) of Roman Date.Finders: Wrexhan Heritage Society Description of FindThis small group of second century AD copper alloy coins contains examples spanning the reigns of the emperors Hadrian, Antoninus Pius, Marcus Aurelius and Commodus and their families. (High degree of corrosion prevents close catalogue identification in many cases). The latest identifiable coin is for the deified Marcus Aurelius, probably produced very close to the time of his death in AD 180.Summary (all of the Roman brass denomination known as sestertii)Hadrian (AD 117-38) (1)Antoninus Pius (AD 138-61) (1)Faustina I (1)Marcus Aurelius (AD 161-80) (1)Faustina II (1)Lucilla (1)Commodus (AD 180-92) -Divus Marcus (1)Uncertain emperor (6)Total 13DiscussionThis pattern fits well with that which might be expected for a hoard of Roman coins deposited late in the second century AD with older, more worn, issues stretching back over previous reigns.CatalogueHADRIAN (1)1. Illegible (head of Hadrian) Illegible Z ? ? Qt 1. 14.11gREIGN OF ANTONINUS PIUS (2)2. Illegible (head of Antoninus Pius) COS [...] S C (Aequitas stg. l., holding scales and cornucopia) A1* Cf.1824 etc Cf.855 etc Qt 1. 20.39g3. Illegible (head of Faustina I) Illegible Z ? ? Qt 1. 17.93gREIGN OF MARCUS AURELIUS (3)4. Illegible (laur. bust of Marcus) [...] S C (Felicitas stg. l., holding caduceus and sceptre) Z ? ? Qt 1. 18.47g5. [F]AVST]INA [AVGVSTA] [...] S C (Venus Victrix, stg, l.) E2* Cf.956 Cf.1681 Qt 1. 20.82g6. [LVCILL]AE AVG ANTONINI AVG F [VES]TA S C (Pietas stg. l.) E1* 1178 1779 Qt 1. 19.19gREIGN OF COMMODUS (1)7. [DIVVS M ANTO]NINVS PIVS CONSECRATIO // S C in ex. (Marcus std. l., on eagle flying r.) A1+ 394 660 Qt 1. 12.58gEMPEROR UNCERTAIN (6)8. illegible illegible stg. figs. Z ? ? Qt 2. 14.17g, 15.77g9. Illegible Illegible Z ? ? Qt 4. 11.78g, 11.92g, 12.37g, 15.64",
